1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 4-120.4, is
3 amended to read as follows:
4 A. The Secretary of the State Election Board shall accept
5 written notice from the United States Attorney of persons convicted
6 of felonies in a district court of the United States. The Secretary
7 of the State Election Board shall cause the voter registrations of
8 persons listed in the written notice to be cancelled in the county
9 of the person’s residence and shall notify the secretary of the
10 appropriate county election board of the cancellation.
11 B. The Secretary of the State Election Board shall accept
12 written notice from the tribal court clerk of a federally-recognized
13 tribe of persons convicted of felonies in a tribal court in the
14 United States. The Secretary of the State Election Board shall
15 cause the voter registrations of persons listed in the written
16 notice to be cancelled in the county of the person’s residence and
17 shall notify the secretary of the appropriate county election board
18 of the cancellation.
19 C. The court clerk in each county shall prepare a list monthly
20 of all persons convicted in the county of a felony and shall
21 transmit the list to the secretary of the county election board.
22 The list shall include information necessary to identify a person on
23 the list as a registered voter prescribed by the Secretary of the
24 State Election Board. The secretary shall cancel the registration
